						               													<description>RULES (for 3 or 4 players)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;AIM: To collect and arrange five cards in &amp;quot;rock cycle&amp;quot; order. Cards represent &amp;#10;rocks and geological processes, these must be collected and displayed in the &amp;#10;right order depending on the Rock Cycle (see below). Each single card tells &amp;#10;what are the preceding and the following cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The &amp;quot;Burial: heat-pressure&amp;quot; card is very important as it allows the transformation&amp;#10;of a sedimentary/igneous rock into a metamorphic one. It is essential that the &amp;#10;preceding card and the following card are logically ordered. The exact sequence&amp;#10;is described in the &amp;quot;Burial: heat-pressure&amp;quot; card. That means that if you have &amp;#10;&amp;quot;Granite&amp;quot;, you have to link it to &amp;quot;Gneiss&amp;quot; and nothing else.&amp;#10;N.B. Chalk should be treated as Limestone (i.e. changes into &amp;quot;Marble&amp;quot;).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1- Shuffle cards and deal 5 each. Place the remaining deck, face-down, at the &amp;#10;    centre of the table; reveal the first card and place it &amp;quot;face up&amp;quot; next to the deck.&amp;#10;2- Players have to arrange the five cards in &amp;quot;rock cycle&amp;quot; order: each player &amp;#10;    have to decide, according to the cards in his/her hand, which &amp;quot;section&amp;quot; of&amp;#10;    the Rock Cycle would be more convenient to build upon. Players should not&amp;#10;    reveal their cards.&amp;#10;3- In turn, clockwise, each player pick either the top card from the deck or the &amp;#10;    face-up card next to it. Then he/she has to discard one card; this will be placed &amp;#10;    face-up next to the deck. Once the card has been discarded, the next player can &amp;#10;    pick a card and so on.&amp;#10;4- When a player has put all five cards in order he/she will reveal them all and,&amp;#10;     if the other players acknowledge the right order, he/she is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
